  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This UnitOfAssurance evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The intended use is to support a 510(k) submission by demonstrating that predicted hemolysis index under CPB flow rates of 3–6 L/min and rotational speeds of 2000–3500 RPM remains within clinically acceptable thresholds. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-hemolysis-generic-cbp-v3",
